<paragraph id="8BE98519D11049707BF1C32BFC5E3618" blockId="9.[358,1229,541,638]" box="[655,933,612,638]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">
<figureCitation id="136D999CD11049707BF1C32BFD173618" box="[655,748,612,638]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1737,1763]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,274,1681]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[189,1398,268,1681]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. Wing venation of the species described here. A. Belyta knudhoejgaardi sp. nov. B. Cinetus breviscapus sp. nov.C. Cinetus elongatus sp. nov.D. Pantoclis globosasp. nov. E. Pantolyta augustinusii sp. nov. F. Basalys villumi sp. nov. G. Doliopria baltica sp. nov. H. Spilomicrus succinalis sp. nov. Scale bars: A–E = 1 mm; F, H = 0.5 mm; G = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468171/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Figs 1C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="136D999CD11049707B84C32BFCB93618" box="[762,834,612,638]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1814,1840]" captionTargetBox="[260,1327,265,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[260,1327,265,1773]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 3. A–C. Cinetus elongatus sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608402). A. Habitus in lateral view. B. Head in lateral view. C. Mesosoma and petiole in lateral view. D–H. Pantoclis globosa sp. nov. D–F. Holotype (NHMD-608414). D. Habitus in lateral view. E. Habitus in dorsal view. F. Gaster in lateral view. G–H. Paratype (NHMD-608394). G. Habitus in lateral view. H. Habitus in dorsal view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; fe = flagellomere emargination; mtr = metapleural ridge. Scale bars: A = 2 mm; B–E, G–H = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468181" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468181/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">3A–C</figureCitation>
, 
<tableCitation id="C6D4B0A2D11049707A30C32BFC5E3618" box="[846,933,612,638]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="2.[189,259,265,291]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Table 1. Fossil record of the Diapriidae Haliday, 1833 in Baltic amber (1 Pantolyta similis sp. nov. was originally identified as P. macrocera (Thomson, 1858))." pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Table 1</tableCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D110497079C3C3EAFD08371D" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D110497079C3C3EAFECD36D9" blockId="9.[189,310,677,703]" box="[189,310,677,703]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">
<heading id="D0A13275D110497079C3C3EAFECD36D9" bold="true" box="[189,310,677,703]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD110497079C3C3EAFECD36D9" bold="true" box="[189,310,677,703]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D110497079C3C39BFD08371D" blockId="9.[188,1401,724,891]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">
Scape longer than head length, F1 longest flagellomere, deeply emarginated on anterior half, wider at apex of emargination (male; 
<figureCitation id="136D999CD11049707B46C3B8FD413777" box="[568,698,759,785]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1814,1840]" captionTargetBox="[260,1327,265,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[260,1327,265,1773]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 3. A–C. Cinetus elongatus sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608402). A. Habitus in lateral view. B. Head in lateral view. C. Mesosoma and petiole in lateral view. D–H. Pantoclis globosa sp. nov. D–F. Holotype (NHMD-608414). D. Habitus in lateral view. E. Habitus in dorsal view. F. Gaster in lateral view. G–H. Paratype (NHMD-608394). G. Habitus in lateral view. H. Habitus in dorsal view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; fe = flagellomere emargination; mtr = metapleural ridge. Scale bars: A = 2 mm; B–E, G–H = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468181" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468181/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Fig. 3A–B</figureCitation>
); metapleural carina extending from hind coxa and forked anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="136D999CD1104970783FC255FE673753" box="[321,412,794,821]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1814,1840]" captionTargetBox="[260,1327,265,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[260,1327,265,1773]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 3. A–C. Cinetus elongatus sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608402). A. Habitus in lateral view. B. Head in lateral view. C. Mesosoma and petiole in lateral view. D–H. Pantoclis globosa sp. nov. D–F. Holotype (NHMD-608414). D. Habitus in lateral view. E. Habitus in dorsal view. F. Gaster in lateral view. G–H. Paratype (NHMD-608394). G. Habitus in lateral view. H. Habitus in dorsal view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; fe = flagellomere emargination; mtr = metapleural ridge. Scale bars: A = 2 mm; B–E, G–H = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468181" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468181/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); marginal vein slightly shorter than its distance from basal vein, radial cell elongate, longer than marginal vein, postmarginal vein 1.5 times as long as radial cell (
<figureCitation id="136D999CD11049707D3CC271FB66373E" box="[1090,1181,830,856]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1737,1763]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,274,1681]" captionTargetId="figure-17@6.[189,1398,268,1681]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 1. Wing venation of the species described here. A. Belyta knudhoejgaardi sp. nov. B. Cinetus breviscapus sp. nov.C. Cinetus elongatus sp. nov.D. Pantoclis globosasp. nov. E. Pantolyta augustinusii sp. nov. F. Basalys villumi sp. nov. G. Doliopria baltica sp. nov. H. Spilomicrus succinalis sp. nov. Scale bars: A–E = 1 mm; F, H = 0.5 mm; G = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468171" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468171/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
); petiole 5.3 times as long as wide, with a few long setae (
<figureCitation id="136D999CD11049707BF7C22EFD1E371D" box="[649,741,865,891]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1814,1840]" captionTargetBox="[260,1327,265,1773]" captionTargetId="figure-17@10.[260,1327,265,1773]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 3. A–C. Cinetus elongatus sp. nov., holotype (NHMD-608402). A. Habitus in lateral view. B. Head in lateral view. C. Mesosoma and petiole in lateral view. D–H. Pantoclis globosa sp. nov. D–F. Holotype (NHMD-608414). D. Habitus in lateral view. E. Habitus in dorsal view. F. Gaster in lateral view. G–H. Paratype (NHMD-608394). G. Habitus in lateral view. H. Habitus in dorsal view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; fe = flagellomere emargination; mtr = metapleural ridge. Scale bars: A = 2 mm; B–E, G–H = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468181" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468181/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D110497079C3C2EDFE323068" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D110497079C3C2EDFEBF37DA" blockId="9.[189,324,930,956]" box="[189,324,930,956]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">
<heading id="D0A13275D110497079C3C2EDFEBF37DA" bold="true" box="[189,324,930,956]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD110497079C3C2EDFEBF37DA" bold="true" box="[189,324,930,956]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D110497079C3C29EFE323068" blockId="9.[189,1399,977,1039]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">The species name derives from the general elongate aspect of the species. The specific epithet is to be treated as an adjective.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
