<paragraph id="8BE98519D110497079C3C5EAFE3930D9" blockId="9.[189,450,1189,1215]" box="[189,450,1189,1215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">
<heading id="D0A13275D110497079C3C5EAFE3930D9" bold="true" box="[189,450,1189,1215]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD110497079C3C5EAFE3930D9" bold="true" box="[189,450,1189,1215]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Locality and horizon</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D110497079C3C59BFBC53088" blockId="9.[189,1086,1236,1262]" box="[189,1086,1236,1262]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Baltic amber is considered to be of Bartonian–Priabonian age, ca 34–38 Ma.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D110497279C3C45AFEC23630" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D110497079C3C45AFEB53149" blockId="9.[189,334,1301,1327]" box="[189,334,1301,1327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">
<heading id="D0A13275D110497079C3C45AFEB53149" bold="true" box="[189,334,1301,1327]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD110497079C3C45AFEB53149" bold="true" box="[189,334,1301,1327]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11049707994C40BFED13138" blockId="9.[188,1400,1348,1656]" box="[234,298,1348,1374]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11049707994C40BFED13138" bold="true" box="[234,298,1348,1374]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D110497079C3C427FD713211" blockId="9.[188,1400,1348,1656]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">
BODY. 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11049707872C428FE8C31E4" box="[268,375,1383,1410]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.46" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="4.46">4.46 mm</quantity>
. Head higher than long, homogeneously pubescent (HeL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11049707D54C428FB6C31E4" box="[1066,1175,1383,1410]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="0.54">0.54 mm</quantity>
); eye oval; antenna inserted on distinct shelf; toruli broadly separated; antenna with numerous short hairs; scape longer than head length; pedicel more than two times as short as shortest flagellomere, almost as wide as long; flagellomeres cylindrical, elongate, much longer than wide; F1 longest, with deep emargination basally, wider at apex of emargination; F2–F11 shorter, slightly decreasing in length; F12 longer than F7–F11, conical (antennomeres length of 
<typeStatus id="54ED3BBBD11049707B43C758FD5C3257" box="[573,679,1559,1585]" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">holotype</typeStatus>
, in mm: Sc-0.61; P-0.12; F1-0.41; F2-0.38; F3-0.36; F4-0.34; F5-0.35; F6-0.33; F7-0.31; F8-0.32; F9-0.29; F10-0.29; F11-0.26; F12-0.33); mandibles of ordinary form, bidentate, slightly crossing at tip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D110497279C3C7D0FEA63520" blockId="9.[188,1401,1695,2003]" lastBlockId="11.[189,1399,265,326]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="9" pageNumber="66">
MESOSOMA. Pubescent, with short setae (MsL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11049707B94C7D0FCAC32DF" box="[746,855,1695,1722]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.52" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="1.52">1.52 mm</quantity>
); pronotum reduced in length, epomia present; mesoscutum large, convex, notauli complete, convergent anteriorly, slightly diverging posteriorly but terminating in anterior scutellar pit; anterior scutellar pit deep, large, suboval with posterior margin convex; metapleural carina distinct, forked anteriorly; propodeum with plicae, median propodeal keel simple. Fore wing extending beyond metasoma, homogeneously micro-pubescent (FwL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11049707D84C663FA913320" box="[1274,1386,1836,1862]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.89" pageId="9" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="3.89">3.89 mm</quantity>
); C, Sc+R, basal vein, M+Cu, M, Cu, marginal vein, postmarginal vein, r-rs and Rs fully pigmented; marginal vein slightly shorter than its distance from basal vein; r-rs well developed; Rs closing radial cell in straight line; radial cell elongate, longer than marginal vein; postmarginal vein 1.5 times as long as radial cell. Hind wing shorter and narrower than fore wing; C pigmented; basal cell opened; three hamuli present. Legs slender, bearing numerous un-organized setae; tibial spur formula 1-2-2; tarsal claws simple.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF29D591D113497379C3C659FD743387" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6468181" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6468181" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6468181/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="67" startId="10.[189,232,1814,1840]" targetBox="[260,1327,265,1773]" targetPageId="10">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D113497379C3C659FD743387" blockId="10.[187,1399,1814,2017]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B922590BD113497379C3C659FEB13356" bold="true" box="[189,330,1814,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">Fig. 3. A–C</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11349737826C658FDD13356" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[344,554,1814,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11349737826C658FDD13356" box="[344,554,1814,1841]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">Cinetus elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11349737B4EC658FD773357" box="[560,652,1815,1841]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype (NHMD-608402). 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11349737A9EC659FC0E3356" bold="true" box="[992,1013,1814,1840]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">A</emphasis>
. Habitus in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11349737C68C658FAD13357" bold="true" box="[1302,1322,1815,1841]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">B</emphasis>
. Head in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11349737815C676FE7B3335" bold="true" box="[363,384,1849,1875]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">C</emphasis>
. Mesosoma and petiole in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11349737A36C675FC783332" bold="true" box="[840,899,1850,1876]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">D–H</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11349737AEFC675FB993332" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[913,1122,1850,1876]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Pantoclis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11349737AEFC675FB993332" box="[913,1122,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">Pantoclis globosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11349737D19C675FB3B3332" box="[1127,1216,1850,1876]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="B922590BD11349737DBBC675FB013332" bold="true" box="[1221,1274,1850,1876]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">D–F</emphasis>
. Holotype (NHMD-608414). 
<emphasis id="B922590BD113497378E1C612FE4F3311" bold="true" box="[415,436,1885,1911]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">D</emphasis>
. Habitus in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11349737B8CC612FCFD3311" bold="true" box="[754,774,1885,1911]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">E</emphasis>
. Habitus in dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11349737D3CC612FBAF3311" bold="true" box="[1090,1108,1885,1911]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">F</emphasis>
. Gaster in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD113497379C3C6CFFF0133FC" bold="true" box="[189,250,1920,1946]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">G–H</emphasis>
. Paratype (NHMD-608394). 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11349737B2DC6CFFD9133FC" bold="true" box="[595,618,1920,1946]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">G</emphasis>
. Habitus in lateral view. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11349737AF1C6CFFC5D33FC" bold="true" box="[911,934,1920,1946]" pageId="10" pageNumber="67">H</emphasis>
. Habitus in dorsal view. Abbreviations: asp = anterior scutellar pit; fe = flagellomere emargination; mtr = metapleural ridge. Scale bars: A = 2 mm; B–E, G–H = 1 mm; F = 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D112497279C3C021FD123597" blockId="11.[189,1399,365,498]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">
METASOMA. Petiole 5.3 times as long as wide (PtL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11249727A56C021FC6E35EE" box="[808,917,366,392]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="0.79">0.79 mm</quantity>
; PtW = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11249727A88C022FB9835EE" box="[1014,1123,365,392]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
), longitudinally ribbed, with sparse very long setae; gaster ellipsoidal (GL = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11249727A4DC0DEFC5B35CD" box="[819,928,401,427]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.61" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="1.61">1.61 mm</quantity>
; GH = 
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11249727A87C0DEFB9C35CD" box="[1017,1127,401,427]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.8" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="0.68">0.68 mm</quantity>
), pointed at apex, with sparse setae on first segments, more numerous at apex; T2 and S2 longest; four ring-like segments posterior to large tergite, genitalia externalized.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D11249727994C356FEBE3655" blockId="11.[189,325,537,598]" box="[234,325,537,563]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727994C356FEBE3655" bold="true" box="[234,325,537,563]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D112497279C3C373FEC23630" blockId="11.[189,325,537,598]" box="[189,313,572,598]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34CD692D112497279C3C332FBB230C8" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE98519D112497279C3C332FEBF36F1" blockId="11.[189,324,637,663]" box="[189,324,637,663]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">
<heading id="D0A13275D112497279C3C332FEBF36F1" bold="true" box="[189,324,637,663]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B922590BD112497279C3C332FEBF36F1" bold="true" box="[189,324,637,663]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D112497279C3C3E3FA8C37DA" blockId="11.[189,1399,684,957]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">
Using 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11249727872C3E3FE3B36A1" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[268,448,684,711]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon’s (1957)</bibRefCitation>
key, 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11249727B7DC3E3FD2C36A0" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[515,727,684,710]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727B7DC3E3FD2C36A0" box="[515,727,684,710]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Cinetus elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11249727BA0C3E3FCC036A0" box="[734,827,684,710]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
keys out near 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727A92C3E3FB7336A0" box="[1004,1160,684,710]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Leptorhaptus</emphasis>
Förster, 1865 sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D112497279C3C380FEA4368C" author="Nixon G. E. J." box="[189,351,719,746]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref15689" refString="Nixon G. E. J. 1957. Hymenoptera, Proctotrupoidea, Diapriidae, subfamily Belytinae. Handbooks for the Identification of British Insects 8 (dii): 1 - 107. https: // doi. org / 10.5281 / zenodo. 23920" type="journal article" year="1957">Nixon (1957)</bibRefCitation>
because of the following characters: fourth antennal segment not modified, mandibles of ordinary form, scutellum without a row of foveae along posterior margin, marginal vein hardly shorter than the radial cell, petiole much longer than wide, notauli subparallel, terminates in scutellar hollow. 
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727862C276FE433735" box="[284,440,825,851]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Leptorhaptus</emphasis>
is currently regarded as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11249727AFBC276FB633735" authority="(Masner 1964)" baseAuthorityName="Masner" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[901,1176,824,851]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727AFBC276FC243735" box="[901,991,825,851]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Cinetus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11249727A93C276FB753735" author="Masner L." box="[1005,1166,824,851]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" pagination="123 - 155" refId="ref15527" refString="Masner L. 1964. A comparison of some Nearctic and Palaearctic genera of Proctotrupoidea (Hymenoptera) with revisional notes. Casopis Ceskoslovenske Spolecnosti Entomologicke 61: 123 - 155." type="journal article" year="1964">Masner 1964</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11249727DDDC276FA8C3735" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[1187,1399,825,851]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727DDDC276FA8C3735" box="[1187,1399,825,851]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Cinetus elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
displays all the diagnostic characters of 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11249727BEFC213FD103710" baseAuthorityName="Masner" baseAuthorityYear="1964" box="[657,747,860,886]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727BEFC213FD103710" box="[657,747,860,886]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Cinetus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC7F8E8D11249727AF8C213FB303710" author="Quadros A. L. &amp; Brandao C. R. F." box="[902,1227,860,886]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" pagination="57 - 91" refId="ref16034" refString="Quadros A. L. &amp; Brandao C. R. F. 2017. Genera of Belytinae (Hymenoptera: Diapriidae) recorded in the Atlantic dense ombrophilous forest from Paraiba to Santa Catarina, Brazil. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia 57 (6): 57 - 91. https: // doi. org / 10.11606 / 0031 - 1049.2017.57.06" type="journal article" year="2017">Quadros &amp; Brandão (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, especially the large anterior scutellar pit, the posterior extremity of notauli directed toward a point within the anterior scutellar pit, the marginal vein shorter than radial cell and slightly shorter than its distance to basal vein.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE98519D112497279C3C2ABFBB230C8" blockId="11.[188,1399,996,1198]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">
Among the Baltic amber species, it differs from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11249727A2FC2ABFBF13798" box="[849,1034,996,1022]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727A2FC2ABFC503798" box="[849,939,996,1022]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Cinetus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
as follow: 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11249727DEBC2ABFAEC3798" authorityName="Szabo &amp; Oehlke" authorityYear="1986" box="[1173,1303,996,1022]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="balticus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727DEBC2ABFAEC3798" box="[1173,1303,996,1022]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">C. balticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the scape as long as F1 (longer in 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11249727B68C548FD133047" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[534,744,1031,1057]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727B68C548FD133047" box="[534,744,1031,1057]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Cinetus elongatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11249727B91C548FCB73047" box="[751,844,1031,1057]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), the petiole shorter (ratio length/middle height: 4 vs 5.3) and the marginal vein longer than its distance from basal vein; 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11249727A83C565FB133022" authority="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen, 2022" authorityName="Brazidec &amp; Vilhelmsen" authorityYear="2022" box="[1021,1256,1066,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviscapus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727A83C565FB133022" box="[1021,1256,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">Cinetus breviscapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A211E470D11249727D8EC564FAB23023" box="[1264,1353,1067,1093]" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has the scape shorter than F1, the petiole shorter (ratio length/middle height: 2.8), the marginal vein longer than its distance from basal vein and the postmarginal vein shorter than radial cell; 
<taxonomicName id="4C56FE9AD11249727DD3C53EFACA30EC" authorityName="Maneval" authorityYear="1938" box="[1197,1329,1136,1163]" class="Insecta" family="Diapriidae" genus="Cinetus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inclusus">
<emphasis id="B922590BD11249727DD3C53EFACA30EC" box="[1197,1329,1136,1163]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="68">C. inclusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a shorter petiole (ratio length/middle height: 1.5) and a smaller body (
<quantity id="4CAE28FCD11249727AA3C5DBFBC630C8" box="[989,1085,1172,1198]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="11" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
